that's listed on that site.

00:17:15.099 --> 00:17:19.800
So I would say there
are probably more.

00:17:19.800 --> 00:17:24.250
So the question is-- and
this gets back to the graphs

00:17:24.250 --> 00:17:27.040
that I showed before--
because there's obviously

00:17:27.040 --> 00:17:29.720
no market for it, it doesn't
necessarily make sense.

00:17:29.720 --> 00:17:33.180
I wouldn't argue for example,
that it's a travesty that DARPA

00:17:33.180 --> 00:17:37.590
didn't invest $100 billion into
solving this prosthetic arm

00:17:37.590 --> 00:17:40.080
problem, because
the same could be

00:17:40.080 --> 00:17:41.770
said for any of
these other orphans.

00:17:41.770 --> 00:17:44.477
We simply can't
afford to do that

00:17:44.477 --> 00:17:45.810
from a public health standpoint.

00:17:45.810 --> 00:17:48.960
It's just not an effective
way to spend our resources.

00:17:48.960 --> 00:17:51.630
So nevertheless,
feeling like this

00:17:51.630 --> 00:17:55.130
is a problem that we'd
like for society to solve

00:17:55.130 --> 00:17:58.560
and that it's not
the only one, this

00:17:58.560 --> 00:18:02.750
is the question-- how can
we attack these problems

00:18:02.750 --> 00:18:04.260
and solve some of them?

00:18:04.260 --> 00:18:06.980
And it's clear that
we probably need

00:18:06.980 --> 00:18:11.130
to think about them a little bit
different way than we are now.

00:18:11.130 --> 00:18:13.810
My friend Chuck
